race.comment: DON'TDOUBTHELADY (1) resumes and looks beautifully placed to kick off her prep in style. The Taylor filly showed real promise last campaign, progressing through the grades before tackling Listed company in The Phoenix at Eagle Farm. That run is easily forgiven, and her sharp trial work suggests she's come back well. Was a dominant winner here first-up last prep and from the good draw with Wiggins aboard, she looks impossible to go past. RAFF VADER (4) charged home late last start and with his light weight, he'll be flying late again. PENSEUR POSITIF (2) is honest and back to a winning trip, while LOST LAMB (5) deserves respect after breaking through. Include in exotics.
